<header>
<h1 class="blog--title">This Week in Spring - March 17th, 2015</h1>
<div class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon engineering"></div>
<a class="category">Engineering</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/fb22593caf24e4bb4c98d467cdd247e6?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" rel="author" href="/team/jlong">Josh Long</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2015-03-17 21:18:00.0">March 17, 2015</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="2030" href="/blog/2015/03/17/this-week-in-spring-march-17th-2015#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</div>
</header>
<div class="blog--post"><p>Welcome to another installment of <em>This Week in Spring</em>! This week I&rsquo;ve been busily preparin for a workshop <a href="http://qconsp.com/speaker/josh-long">I&rsquo;ll be giving at QCon São Paulo next week</a>. If you&rsquo;re at the show, I hope you&rsquo;ll come out to say hi, ask questions and we&rsquo;ll talk Spring and Cloud Foundry. <strong>Obrigado</strong>!</p>
<ol>
<li>The replay on my humble webinar <a href="https://spring.io/blog/2015/03/12/webinar-replay-introducing-spring-session">introducing Spring Session is online, check it out</a>!</li>
<li>Janne Valkealahti has just announced the latest release <a href="https://spring.io/blog/2015/03/11/spring-security-kerberos-1-0-0-rc1-released">of Spring Security Kerberos 1.0.0.RC1</a>, packed with new features and now - at long last!! - near GA! Go Janne and team, go!</li>
<li>Spring and Groovy &amp; Grails Tool Suite lead <a href="https://spring.io/blog/2015/03/11/spring-tool-suite-and-groovy-grails-tool-suite-3-6-4-released">Martin Lippert just announced STS and GGTS 3.6.4</a>.</li>
<li>I put together a post <a href="https://spring.io/blog/2015/03/16/getting-started-with-couchbase-and-spring-data-couchbase">on getting started with Spring Data Couchbase</a></li>
<li>Spring XD ninjas Marius Bogoevici and Dr. Mark Pollack are going to be giving a webinar on April 28th that <a href="https://spring.io/blog/2015/03/17/webinar-reactive-data-pipelines-with-spring-xd-and-kafka">introduces using Spring XD and Apache Kafka</a> to create reactive data-pipelines.</li>
<li>I&rsquo;ll be giving a webinar on April 21st that introduces <a href="https://spring.io/blog/2015/03/17/webinar-smarter-service-to-service-invocations-with-spring-cloud">how to make smart service-to-service calls with Spring Cloud</a>.</li>
<li>This Week&rsquo;s SpringOne2GX 2014 replays are out! Check out <a href="https://spring.io/blog/2015/03/17/springone2gx-2014-replay-asychronous-design-with-spring-and-rti-1m-events-per-second">Asychronous design with Spring and RTI: 1M events per second</a>, <a href="https://spring.io/blog/2015/03/17/springone2gx-2014-replay-building-a-recommendation-engine-with-spring-and-hadoop">Building a Recommendation Engine with Spring and Hadoop</a>, and author Peter Harrington&rsquo;s <a href="https://spring.io/blog/2015/03/17/springone2gx-2014-replay-become-a-data-driven-organization-with-machine-learning">Become a data-driven Organization with Machine Learning</a>.</li>
<li>Curious about the why Pivotal considers iteself at the nexus of <a href="https://spring.io/blog/2015/03/17/springone2gx-2014-replay-apps-data-cloud-what-does-it-all-mean">Apps, Data and Cloud</a>? Check out Matt Stine&rsquo;s SpringOne2GX replay for the answer.</li>
<li>the Vaadin web framework now has <a href="https://vaadin.com/wiki/-/wiki/Main/Vaadin+Spring"><strong>official</strong> support for Spring and Spring Boot</a>. This support is the official stamping of the <a href="https://github.com/peholmst/vaadin4spring">code that Peter Holmst and I started</a>, so I couldn&rsquo;t be more excited to see how far it&rsquo;s come and to see it finally graduate to an officially supported module.</li>
<li>Intellij 14.1 is packed with all sorts of amazing Spring Boot goodness! Check out this post from <a href="http://blog.jetbrains.com/idea/2015/03/develop-spring-boot-applications-more-productively-with-intellij-idea-14-1/">JetBrain&rsquo;s Yann Cébron on some of the amazing new features</a> and be sure to register for this March webinar in March with our <a href="http://info.jetbrains.com/IDEA-Webinar-March2015-registration.html">own Stéphane Nicoll and Yann</a> covering some of these amazing features!</li>
<li>Heroku have put together a nice writeup <a href="https://blog.heroku.com/archives/2015/3/3/managing_your_microservices_on_heroku_with_netflix_s_eureka">on using Spring Cloud to build cloud native applications on Heroku</a></li>
<li>Check out this video of <a href="http://www.infoq.com/interviews/spring-today-past-and-future">Spring framework lead Juergen Hoeller recorded from Voxxed Days Austria</a></li>
<li>Alex Williams put together a nice post <a href="http://thenewstack.io/cloud-foundry-and-apache-brooklyn-for-automating-paas-with-a-service-broker/">on using Apache Brooklyn - an application blueprint and management system which supports a wide range of software and services in the cloud - to automate Cloud Foundry with their custom service broker</a>. The idea is simple: a Cloud Foundry service broker talks to backend services (it&rsquo;s what drives the flow from <code>cf services</code> and <code>cf create-service</code>). Apache Brooklyn exposed as a service broker in this way is powerful; you only need one broker to expose the catalog of Brooklyn blueprints.</li>
<li>Our pal Matt Stine just published a free e-book for O&rsquo;Reilly on <a href="https://blog.pivotal.io/cloud-foundry-pivotal/news-2/new-book-explains-how-cloud-native-application-architectures-drive-the-innovation-cycle">building cloud-native architectures</a>.</li>
<li>There are a few case studies on the Pivotal blog today. First, Jarrod Vawdrey&rsquo;s post on using data-science to <a href="https://blog.pivotal.io/data-science-pivotal/case-studies-2/using-data-science-to-predict-tv-viewer-behavior-and-formulate-a-hit-tv-show">predict TV viewer behavior and formulate a hit TV show is awesome</a></li>
<li>Dwayne Forde has put together a nice case study on <a href="https://blog.pivotal.io/cloud-foundry-pivotal/case-studies-2/how-pivotal-performs-continuous-delivery-of-mobile-services">How Pivotal Performs Continuous Delivery of Mobile Services</a>.</li>
</ol></div>
</div>
